   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>MH 4482, recto: (1) The name of the centurion (2) who hanged Jesus to the cross was M (3) ...oter.  The king (was) (4) Tiberias.  The name (sic) of the Magi, (5) those who came out of (6) the East, were these: Bathezora, (7) who was the one who brought (8) the gold, and (9) Melchior, who (10) was MH 4482, verso: (1) the one who brought frankincense, (2) and Thaddias, who was (3) the one who brought the myrrh.  (4) And they worshipped him, (5) saying: 'The king of kings (6) is he, the one (7) to whom belongs (8) the glory.&amp;apos</ab>
         </div>
